May 3, 2016 8:17 AM
Hyatt Hotels 1Q results top Street, revenue metric improves
The Associated Press
LinkedIn
Google+
Pinterest
Reddit
Print
Order Reprint of this Story
CHICAGO
Hyatt's first-quarter performance topped analysts' expectations as a key revenue metric improved.For the period ended March 31, the hotel operator earned $34 million, or 25 cents per share. A year earlier the Chicago-based company earned $22 million, or 15 cents per share.That's a penny better than what analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research forecast.Hyatt Hotels Corp. said Tuesday that revenue rose to $1.09 billion from $1.05 billion. Analysts expected $1.08 billion in revenue, according to analysts polled by Zacks.Comparable systemwide revenue per available room climbed 2.2 percent. Revenue per available room, or revpar, is a key gauge of a lodging company's performance.-----Elements of this story were generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on H at http://www.zacks.com/ap/H
